content.Framework and Engine Familiarization: To develop for Flutter, you will eventually need to become familiar with our processes and conventions.
content.Identify Good First Issues: If you prefer to write code, consider starting with the list of good first issues for Flutter or for Flutter DevTools.
content.Reference Instructions: Reference the respective sections below for further instructions.
content.Understand Processes and Conventions: This section lists the documents that describe these methodologies.

content.Add to Documentation: Contribute to the documentation to improve clarity and coverage.
content.Be Courteous: Be courteous and respectful in all interactions.
content.Contribute API Documentation: Contribute to API documentation with sample code and detailed explanations.
content.Contribute Code: Start contributing code to the Flutter project.
content.Contribute to DevTools: Contribute code to Dart & Flutter DevTools.
content.Create Test Cases: Create test cases to increase test coverage.
content.Do Outreach: Engage in outreach activities to promote Flutter.
content.Familiarize with Issue Hygiene: Learn about issue hygiene and GitHub labels.
content.File Issues on GitHub: File issues on GitHub to report bugs or suggest improvements.
content.Find and File Bug Reports: Find and file bug reports to help improve Flutter.
content.Gain Commit Access: Gain commit access by demonstrating commitment and trustworthiness.
content.Help on Chat Channels: Provide help on chat channels to support the community.
content.Help on Mailing Lists: Assist others by answering questions on mailing lists.
content.Help on Stack Overflow: Answer questions related to Flutter on Stack Overflow.
content.Help with Triage: Assist with triage by following the triage guide.
content.Join #hackers-devrel Discord Channel: Join the #hackers-devrel channel for developer relations activities.
content.Join #hackers-triage Discord Channel: Join the #hackers-triage channel to assist with issue triage.
content.Join Discord: Join the Discord server to connect with the Flutter community.
content.Join Flutter Team: Express your interest in joining the Flutter team.
content.Join flutter-hackers Team: Join the flutter-hackers team on GitHub to gain more access.
content.Read Code of Conduct: Read and adhere to the code of conduct.
content.Set Up Development Environment: Follow the steps to set up a development environment for Flutter.
content.Test Beta Releases: Test beta releases to identify regressions.
content.Triage Bugs: Help triage bugs by reproducing issues and identifying duplicates.

content.Contribute Test Cases: If you want to contribute test cases, you can also submit PRs. See the next section for how to set up your development environment, or ask in #hackers-test on Discord.
content.Engine Development Setup: Setting up your engine development environment, which describes the steps you need to configure your computer to work on Flutter's engine.
content.Follow Style Guide: Our style guide, which includes advice for designing APIs for Flutter, and how to format code in the framework.
content.Framework Development Setup: Setting up your framework development environment, which describes the steps you need to configure your computer to work on Flutter's framework.
content.Interest in QA: If this interests you, you can jump in and submit bug reports without needing anyone's permission!
content.Join Discord: The #quality-assurance channel on our Discord server is a good place to talk about what you're doing.
content.Set Up Development Environment: The following list is ordered: you are strongly recommended to go through these documents in the order presented.
content.Submit Bug Reports: We're especially eager for QA testing when we announce a beta release. See quality assurance for more details.
content.Tree Hygiene: Tree hygiene, which covers how to land a PR, how to do code review, how to handle breaking changes, how to handle regressions, and how to handle post-commit test failures.
content.Use Design Doc Template: Flutter design doc template, which should be used when proposing a new technical design.

content.Join Communication Channels: We communicate primarily over GitHub and Discord.
content.Read Code of Conduct: Our code of conduct stipulates explicitly that everyone must be gracious, respectful, and professional.
content.Read Community Norms: Before you get started, we encourage you to read these documents which describe some of our community norms.
content.Read Contributor Access Page: For more details, see the Contributor access page in our docs.
